# Trivy vulnerability ignore list
# https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#trivyignore

# ============================================================
# postgres image: gosu binary (Go stdlib CVEs)
# ============================================================
# gosu is baked into the postgres:18-alpine base image for privilege
# dropping at container startup. It's built with Go 1.24.6; these CVEs
# are fixed in Go >=1.24.8 but no gosu rebuild is available yet.
# Our image replaces gosu with a symlink to su-exec (C binary) so the
# Go code never executes, but trivy still detects it in lower image layers.
# Remove these once gosu is rebuilt with a patched Go (track upstream:
# https://github.com/tianon/gosu/releases).

CVE-2025-58183
CVE-2025-61726
CVE-2025-61728
CVE-2025-61729
CVE-2025-61730
CVE-2025-68121
